-- Portuguese Stocks Drop Most in 18 Months After S&P Downgrade's Debt Rating
-- Andrew Rummer
-- 2010-04-27T15:36:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/portuguese-stocks-drop-most-in-18-months-after-s-p-downgrade-s-debt-rating.html

          
          
             Portuguese stocks plummeted the
most in 18 months as Standard & Poor’s cut the nation’s credit
rating by two steps to A-.  
 The benchmark PSI-20 Index slumped 404.94, or 5.4 percent,
to 7,152.42, the biggest drop since October 2008.  
          
          


  


        